Hungarian Shares Advance Most in 4 Weeks, Led by OTP Bank, Mol

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-03-24T17:06:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/hungarian-shares-advance-most-in-4-weeks-led-by-otp-bank-mol.html
Hungary’s benchmark equity index
rose the most in four weeks as OTP Bank Nyrt., the country’s
biggest lender, and Mol Nyrt., the largest oil company, jumped
more than 2.5 percent.  The BUX gauge of 12 stocks rose 1.9 percent to 22,840.88 at
its 5 p.m. close in Budapest, its biggest one-day rally since
Feb. 25. OTP added 3.4 percent to 5,575 forint. Mol advanced 2.6
percent to 24,000 forint.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  